definition.value: The concentration of L-2-hydroxyglutaric acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.
Activity or concentration of inosine triphosphate pyrophosphohydrolase (EC 3.6.1.19) in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Reduced erythrocyte uroporphyrinogen III cosynthase activity

definition.value: The concentration of lipoprotein(a) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal. Lipoprotein(a), also known as apolipoprotein(A), is encoded by LPA (HGNC:6667).
The amount of bile acids in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
The amount of bile acids in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside the limits of normal.

label.value: Failure to elevate lactate upon ischemic exercise test

definition.value: The concentration of cholestanol in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal. Cholestanol is the 5-alpha-dihydro derivative of cholesterol.

The amount of an organic compound in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside the limits of normal. An organic compound is defined here as a chemical compound that contains a carbon-hydrogen or carbon-carbon bond, although some other definitions exist. Examples of organic compounds includes alkanes, alkenes, alkynes, aromatic compounds, alcohols, ketones, aldehydes, carboxylic acids, and esters.

The amount of a porphyrin compound in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. Porphrins are natural pigments containing a fundamental skeleton of four pyrrole nuclei united through the alpha-positions by four methine groups to form a macrocyclic structure. Porpyrins giove rise to heme and combalamine.
The amount of a coproporphyrin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label.value: Positive cutaneous herpes simplex virus nucleic acid test
Positive CSF mycobacterium tuberculosis nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of Mycobacterium tuberculosis nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.
Growth of mycobacterium in a culture derived from cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label.value: Positive treponema pallidum PCR test in the blood circulation
Positive human Immunodeficiency virus nucleic acid test in the blood circulation

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of human immunodeficiency vrus (HIV) in the blood circulation by a methiod such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label.value: Positive CSF enterovirus nucleic acid test
Positive CSF Borrelia burgdorferi nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of Borrelia burgdorferi nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label.value: Positive CSF arbovirus nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of arbovus nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR..
